restaurant.name: Pizza Mercato
restaurant.description: Pizza Mercato serves up all kinds of pizza, pasta, and sandwiches.
restaurant.landmark: Corner of Mercer & Waverly Place (1 block west of Broadway)

restaurant.name: Empire Szechuan Village
restaurant.description: Empire Szechuan Village has established itself as a cornerstone of the Greenwich Village community since 1985 by providing excellent service and great food. They feature selections in both Chinese and Japanese cuisine and also have a vegetarian section on the menu.If you require eating utensils, please indicate so in the special instructions field located in the checkout screen.

restaurant.name: Two Boots To Go West
restaurant.description: The "two boots" are Louisiana and Italy, and Two Boots to Go West is combining the cuisines of these regions on top of pizza pies. If you're craving Cajun food and pizza, order one of Two-Boots' specialty pies.

restaurant.name: Istanbul Grill
restaurant.description: This neighborhood Turkish restaurant has a lot to offer. From delicious appetizers and fresh vegetarian salads to main courses and hot, just off the grill kebab platters, there is always something for everyone. Istanbul Grill also serves soups, side orders, desserts, and beverages. Order from Istanbul Grill for a real taste of Mediterranean cuisine.

restaurant.name: Boyd Thai
restaurant.description: Boyd Thai serves up authentic Thai food, including Pad Thai, curries, salads, and noodle dishes. Levels of spiciness can be adjusted according to the customer's taste buds!

restaurant.name: Bone Lick Park BBQ
restaurant.description: At Bone Lick Park BBQ, the meats are slow-cooked (16 hours!) in a fruit-wood smoker. Order tender barbecue, tasty sandwiches, and hearty Southern favorites, like creamy macaroni & cheddar and stewed fresh okra, from Bone Lick Park.True wood-smoked meats display a pink coloration. This should not be mistaken for "rare."

restaurant.name: Atomic Wings @ Down The Hatch
restaurant.description: Order up heaping portions of supercharged American favorites from Atomic Wings. Atomic Wings has lots of appetizers, sandwiches, burgers, hot dogs, and, of course, wings! Get yours with one of the sauces for the sane--Honey Mustard, BBQ--or one of the sauces for the insane--Abusive, Nuclear, Suicidal, Bite Me.

restaurant.name: Bread & Pastry Cafe
restaurant.description: Fresh baked goods, sandwiches, panini, burgers, salads, wraps, and breakfast are served daily at Bread & Pastry Cafe. This humble establishment offers an astounding array of choices for breakfast, lunch, dinner, and anything in between.

restaurant.name: Manatus Restaurant
restaurant.description: Manatus Restaurant is far from your typical greasy spoon: on the menu you'll find a variety of breakfast options, fresh juice, appetizers, 100% pure beef burgers, sandwiches, diet options, Greek & Italian specialties, and desserts. Manatus' menu is so long and comprehensive, everyone is sure to find something they'll love. Order top-quality diner fare from Manatus today.EXCEPT ON TUESDAYS, MANATUS SAUTE SPECIALS ARE SERVED EVERYDAY FROM 4:00pm to 11:30pm.

restaurant.name: Dirty Bird To Go
restaurant.description: With mentions in the New York Times and Daily Candy, you know the chicken at this joint has to be good. Fill up on chicken-comfort favorites like fried chicken, rotisserie chicken, and chicken fingers, plus wraps, sides like mac 'n cheese and smashed potatoes & gravy, and Dirty Bird's "Freshly Baked Bad-Ass Cookies."

restaurant.name: Alberto's Pizza & Cheesesteak Factory
restaurant.cuisines: Philly Steaks, Sandwiches, Pizza, Fast Food

restaurant.name: Kool Bloo
restaurant.description: Offering healthy and non-healthy options 24/7, this eatery features typical American fare. No matter what you are in the mood for, Kool Bloo has something for you.

restaurant.name: Ray's Super Deli
restaurant.description: Ray's Super Deli is a small West Village bodega that will definitely surprise you with the breadth of its menu. Ray's Super Deli features a mix of super-size sandwiches and Latin American specialties. If you aren't craving cow feet soup or a sweet plantain meat cake, Ray's will satisfy your hunger with more low-key sandwiches. Order your simple groceries from Ray's; cold cuts and cheeses are also available to order by the pound.

restaurant.name: Bamboleo Mexican
restaurant.description: Laid-back Mexican fare characterizes Bamboleo's menu, which contains all of the standard Mexican dishes you would expect, plus some extras like Mexican sandwiches.

restaurant.name: Koo Sushi
restaurant.description: Koo Sushi is serving up simple and inexpensive Japanese food. Dozens of rolls--both classic and more unique--are available from this small Japanese eatery.

restaurant.name: Masamoto Japanese
restaurant.description: This Japanese restaurant offers an extensive menu, including hibachi, teriyaki, and dozens of sushi appetizers and entrees. NYU students receive a 10% discount when NYU student ID is presented.

restaurant.name: Cafe Espanol
restaurant.description: Cafe Espanol offers patrons a wide variety of authentic Spanish cuisine. Specialty items include paella flavored with real wild saffron, imported Spanish manchego cheese, and Serrano ham or imported pulpo. All of these high-quality ingredients come together to give the diner the best possible tapas experience! Order a variety of small plates to sample at home or share with friends.

restaurant.name: Ditch Plains
restaurant.description: This sleek restaurant features high-quality seafood shack fare and comfort classics with a twist. Definitely try some fish or steak dishes, but save room for dessert! Ditch Plains is serving up 'smores, deep fried mini candy bars, and their Ditch 'Wich ice cream sandwich to give your meal a sweet finale.

restaurant.name: Good Restaurant
restaurant.description: Good Restaurant opened in March 2000, offering a moderately priced contemporary American menu in a casual, stylish setting. Chef/Owner Steven Picker develops dishes that are all-American in spirit utilizing fresh, seasonal ingredients. Good Restaurant takes pride in providing the casual bite with its well-rounded dinner menu of familiar dishes given the modern twist. Their Lunch Counter offers freshly made seasonal sandwiches, salads, snacks and sweets packaged for quick grab n' go.

restaurant.name: Caliente Cab Co.
restaurant.description: Caliente Cab Company ushered in a new wave of Mexican Restaurants to the Big Apple over two decades ago when, in 1984, Dos Crazy Mexican Cab Drivers presented authentic sizzling fajitas and legendary frozen margaritas to New Yorkers for the first time. Caliente Cab Co. features generous portions of fresh, premium, Tex-Mex and traditional Mexican food.

restaurant.name: Salon de Tapas
restaurant.description: Order Spanish favorites from Salon de Tapas. An extensive tapas menu with items like gambas al ajillo, jamon serrano, and tostones (fried green bananas) is matched with popular Spanish entrees and several salads.

restaurant.name: Tapas on Carmine
restaurant.description: Tapas on Carmine offers patrons a wide variety of authentic Spanish cuisine. Specialty items include paella flavored with real wild saffron, imported Spanish manchego cheese, and Serrano ham or imported pulpo. All of these high-quality ingredients come together to give the diner the best possible tapas experience! Order a variety of small plates to sample at home or share with friends.

restaurant.name: Focacceria
restaurant.description: Focaccia sandwiches and pasta dishes form the center point of Focacceria's menu of Italian favorites. Choose your own type of pasta for each pasta dish!

restaurant.name: BBQ Pit (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Beyond Thai Kitchen
restaurant.description: For a wide variety of signature Thai dishes, check out Beyond Thai Kitchen. Their lunch specials are sure to bring some of the exotic to your afternoon; also check out noodle, rice, curry, and special dinner entrees.

restaurant.name: Isle Thai Home Cooking
restaurant.description: For classic Thai dishes--noodles, curries, and specialty Thai entrees--order from Isle Thai. The menu is full of Thai favorites, with plenty of appetizers and soups to start off your meal. Try one of Thai Isle's main plates for lunch, which come with a free starter!

restaurant.name: Cucina Stagionale Restaurant/Bar
restaurant.description: For unpretentious, high-quality Italian-American comfort food, order from Cucina Stagionale. You're sure to find filling, hearty Italian dishes on their extensive menu that will satisfy any craving for a good red-sauce dinner.

restaurant.name: Hudson Falafel
restaurant.description: This eatery is serving up Middle Eastern favorites, from hot falafel and meat kababs to tabouli salad, humus, and honey-sweetened desserts. The wide selection of Middle Eastern dishes and snacks features many specialties; order yourself a Middle Eastern feast--or at least some tasty falafel--today!

restaurant.name: Funayama Japanese Restaurant
restaurant.description: Order fresh sushi in the heart of Greenwich Village from Funayama Japanese Restaurant. In addition to sushi, the menu features cooked entrees, salads, soups, and plenty of Japanese appetizers.

restaurant.name: Tanti Baci Caffe
restaurant.description: Tanti Baci Caffé is one of New York Citys most romantic, authentic Italian restaurants. Since 1992, Tanti Baci Caffe has been serving New Yorkers with original Southern and Northern recipes from the old Italian country using all natural and imported ingredients. No wonder customers who try Tanti Baci order again and again!

restaurant.name: Grand Sichuan
restaurant.description: Grand Sichuan is on a mission to raise New Yorkers' appreciation and awareness of high quality Chinese cuisine. The menu features a plethora of lunch specials, and it also includes many noodle dishes, classical Sichuan dishes, and even a section devoted to the latest dishes introduced by the restaurant.

restaurant.name: Pinto Restaurant
restaurant.description: Order New Asian Thai Cuisine from Pinto, which is serving up bold, intense flavors in Thai and French-influenced dishes. Choose from a wide variety of appetizers, main courses, and sides. Pinto's prix fixe lunch get you a choice of one appetizer and one entree, served with Green Salad with Lime Vinaigrette.

restaurant.name: Kobma Thai
restaurant.description: Kobma Thai is serving up Thai food packed with authentic flavors and ingredients like peanut sauce, red and green curries, lemon grass, and chilis. The best part of all? Kobma Thai delivers a great bang for your buck with their affordable, high-quality Thai cuisine.

restaurant.name: Mercadito Grove
restaurant.description: Expertly blending traditional Mexico with creative interpretations of local and seasonal ingredients is the inspiration behind Mercadito. Order the Guacamole Tasting for classic and unique guacs, ceviche, botanas, tacos, and full dinner plates from Mercadito Grove.

restaurant.name: The Sullivan Bistro (formerly the Sullivan Diner)
restaurant.description: Sullivan Bistro is bringing "Bistronomy"--the trend of combining basic bistro decor with quality cuisine--to the West Village. The eclectic American menu, with French touches, offers something for everyone, whether for breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

restaurant.name: Bleecker Street Pizza
restaurant.description: The Bleecker Street authentic Tuscan thin-crust pizza from a family recipe passed through the generations. Nonna Maria left her birthplace of Tuscany at age nineteen, bringing with her the family recipe for this delectable pizza. Experience the tantalizing aroma and sublime flavor of this real Italian specialty pizza in New York City! Winner, Best Pizza in New York via the Food Network, three years running.

restaurant.name: Five Guys Burgers & Fries
restaurant.description: Customize to your heart's delight with a Five Guys burger. Choose from a multitude of toppings--all of which are free--to go with your patties! The menu may be simple, but there are plenty of options when you put a bit of your own taste & imagination into creating the perfect burger & fries pairing.

restaurant.name: Francesco Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Try an order from Francesco Pizzeria for traditional and specialty pizzas, soup, salad, appetizers, entrees, seafood, and pasta. You can even get your pasta on a pizza with Francesco's Baked Ziti Pie, Lasagna Pie, or Penne alla Vodka Pie.

restaurant.name: Baluchi's
restaurant.description: Baluchi's, one of Zagat's top rated Indian restaurants, offers a selection of traditional & regional Indian cuisines that are carefully prepared and presented by experienced chefs. Choose from a wide variety of Indian dishes and Tandoori breads to accompany your meal.

restaurant.name: Ritz Asia
restaurant.description: Asian Fusion takes center stage at Ritz Asia, where a combination of Japanese, Chinese, and Thai specialties are on the extensive menu. Order from a wide array of appetizers, dim sum, sushi, noodles, and gourmet entrees.

restaurant.name: Montes Trattoria
restaurant.description: Monte's Trattoria, a romantic Italian Restaurant located in the heart of Greenwich Village, has existed since 1918. The Mosconi family has continued its rich tradition, and Chef Pietro Mosconi delivers authentic Northen Italian dishes from his region of Emilia Romagna.

restaurant.name: Insomnia Cookies
restaurant.description: Insomnia Cookies is here to serve all of your late-night, sweet-tooth needs. Got a hankering for some hot, fresh-out-of-the-oven cookies at 11PM? Insomnia has got you covered with eleven cookie varieties and brownies, too!Please note: estimated delivery time is 30-45 minutes. Inclement weather may increase the delivery time.

restaurant.name: Karahi
restaurant.description: "Karahi" means "cooking wok," and Karahi is serving up "purifying" Indian cuisine that brings together simplicity and lightness. The refined, rustic offerings on the menu will allow you to fully taste the flavors of traditional ingredients.

restaurant.name: Happy Taco Burrito
restaurant.description: Quick Mexican--fast-food style--is what you'll find from this taco & burrito shop. Some uncommon combinations, like a jack cheese & eel quesadilla, are featured on the menu alongside a plethora of typical Mexican street food favorites.

restaurant.name: The Path Cafe
restaurant.description: The Path Cafe offers the freshest, high-quality ingredients at affordable prices. The cuisine at the Path Cafe has a modern European flare that will go above and beyond your expectation of a simple sandwich, soup or salad. Breakfast and organic coffee are also available to order.

restaurant.name: Freakin' Wings (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Indian Taj
restaurant.description: Craving chicken tikka masala and naan? Order an Indian feast from Indian Taj, a restaurant which boasts a wide selection of common Indian favorites and more unique dishes. The menu features Indian appetizers and vegetarian, seafood, poultry, and meat entrees.

restaurant.name: Monster Pizza
restaurant.description: Founded in 2009, Monster Pizzas is setting itself apart from other pizzerias by offering the freshest ingredients and dessert pizzas. If you're health-conscious, try one of the Healthy Monster pizzas. Love meats? There's a Meat Lovers Monster pie for you!

restaurant.name: Vandam Diner
restaurant.description: In the SoHo neighborhood for over 15 years serving up classical diner fare.

restaurant.name: Antica Venezia
restaurant.description: Antica Venezia presents a menu based on heritage recipes from the breathtaking city of Venice. Order an old-fashioned Italian meal, complete with salads, antipasti, pasta, fish, meat entrees, and Italian desserts from Antica Venezia today.

restaurant.name: Dallas Jones BBQ
restaurant.description: Dallas Jones BBQ (not to be confused with the Dallas BBQ chain) is a family owned and operated barbecue joint. When it was first opened in 1984, Dallas Jones was the first delivery business for BBQ ribs. The restaurant's commitment to BBQ dishes with epicurean tastes has positioned Dallas Jones as a true original and neighborhood favorite.

restaurant.name: CC's Cafe
restaurant.description: CC's Cafe specializes in high-quality breakfast and lunch items. This chic little eatery prepares wraps, sandwiches, and salads along with lots of fresh bakery items, smoothies, coffee and tea.

restaurant.name: Ben's Pizza
restaurant.description: Ben's Pizza is a straight-forward, no-nonsense pizzeria serving up NYC-style pies. The Grand Ma pizza--thin crust, fresh tomato sauce, thick mozzarella--is a customer favorite!

restaurant.name: Energize Me Foods (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Kelley and Ping
restaurant.description: Kelley & Ping serves eclectic, global cuisine with touches of Chinese, Thai, and Korean cooking. Try small dishes, curries, noodles, and entrees, or the lunch box, which comes with a side salad and chicken broth.

restaurant.name: Joe's Pizza
restaurant.description: With superstars Ben Affleck, Kevin Spacey, and Kevin Bacon singing the praises of Joe's Pizza, you know it has to be good. The menu is simple -- pizza, pizza, and more pizza with the toppings of your choice.

restaurant.name: Energy Kitchen
restaurant.description: At Energy Kitchen, no item contains more than 500 calories. By grilling, baking, or steaming everything on the menu, Energy Kitchen makes eating healthy an cinch. Try one of their light and healthy wraps, burgers, salads, or entrees!

restaurant.name: Petit Abeille
restaurant.description: Get acquainted with fine Belgian cuisine at an affordable price by ordering a meal from Petit Abeille. "Petit Abeille" ("little bee"), which gets its name from a popular Belgian children's book of the 1970s, has been awarded praise for its hot chocolate, Belgian waffles, and Moules-frites (mussels with fries). Their delivery menu comes complete with Belgian breakfast, lunch, dinner & dessert options.Cash only

restaurant.name: Pesce Pasta
restaurant.description: Trattoria Pesce Pasta is an Italian restaurant specializing in Northern Italian cuisine. Established in 1993, Pesce Pasta is committed to providing customers with the finest dining experience possible. The menu is full of simple, hearty, and authentic Italian fare.

restaurant.name: AOC Restaurant
restaurant.description: AOC, short for "L'aile ou la cuisse" ("the wing or the thigh"), is named after a 1970s French movie about the virtues of traditional French food. AOC's extensive menu is a combination of handed down family recipes from the chef/owner, Romain Bonnans, and classic French fare. Try French favorites not commonly seen on American menus from AOC.

restaurant.name: Surya
restaurant.description: Surya is a uniquely modern Indian restaurant in the Village serving contemporary Indian cuisine. Chef Lala Sharma employs the best of the Indian culinary tradition, preparing rich, complex dishes that combine a flair for improvisation with a knowledge of health and nutrition. Order a classic dish like Chicken Tikka Masala, or experiment with something new from Surya!

restaurant.name: Moustache Pitza
restaurant.description: Moustache Pitza is rated by "Where the Locals Eat" as the BEST MIDDLE EASTERN in New York City (2009). A step up from hole in the wall but obscure enough to pat yourself on the back for finding it, Moustache serves up some of the freshest jazzed-up versions of Middle Eastern classics around. Order just-out-of-the-oven pita bread and a version of baba ghanoush that defines the dish like Project Runway defines style.

restaurant.name: Do Hwa Restaurant
restaurant.description: Do Hwa is cooking up seasonal and hearty home-style Korean fare. The lunch menu features "Lunch Boxes" of Korean favorites served with seasonal noodles, vegetable dumplings and sautéed red potatoes. The menu also features a wide selection of traditional and imaginative dishes.

restaurant.name: Agave
restaurant.description: Agave features an encyclopedic menu that includes mostly Southwestern fare with some far-reaching global influences. Much of the menu is very Mexican (quesadillas) with unique takes (the Texas quesadilla has wild shrimp, mango pico, and cheese). Order a Southwestern meal full of fresh, high-quality ingredients and inspired combinations today.

restaurant.name: Gusto Ristorante e Bar Americano
restaurant.description: As close to actually dining in Italy as it gets. Gustos gutsy, authentic regional Italian dishes always respect the seasons.

restaurant.name: Ruben's Empanadas
restaurant.description: A well known place for the Mexican specialty. With many varieties and an authentic recipe everyone can find something here.

restaurant.name: Soy Cafe
restaurant.description: Soy Cafe is a neighborhood coffeeshop and cafe located in Manhattan's West Village. The coffee is good, and the food is tasty (and good for you). Soy Cafe's coffee is certified fair-trade organic, delivered weekly from a local roaster in Queens. Soy Cafe offers a full selection of espresso drinks, a killer green tea soy latte, Soyafrosts (blended ice soy drinks) and Soy Soothers (steamed soy milk), made using homemade organic soymilk (100% organic, non-GMO). Don't eat meat? You've found the right place. Soy Cafe's food is all vegan & vegetarian friendly, though they do offer several non-vegetarian dishes for omnivores. Breakfast is served all day and includes pressed bagels with egg whites, avocado, and soy cream cheese. For lunch and dinner, Soy Cafe has a full selection of yummy salads, sandwiches, panini, and crepes.

restaurant.name: Milux Cafe
restaurant.cuisines: Italian, Ice Cream, Cafe, Coffee Bar

restaurant.name: La Pasta Bistro & Grill
restaurant.description: La Pasta Bistro & Grill serves more than just pasta (although they do have a wide selection of pasta dishes). They also offer lots of appetizers, salads, pizza, sandwiches, burgers, entrees, omelets, pancakes, and desserts. Order from La Pasta and everyone will be sure to find a pleasing meal.

restaurant.name: Il Cantuccio
restaurant.description: Il Cantuccio uses entirely authentic recipes when preparing their biscotti, bread, pizza, and focaccia menu items (including Italian sandwiches). With selected prime quality ingredients, careful handmade production, and the respect of the original recipes (no type of fat, preservative or food coloring is used), Il Cantuccio creates Italian specialties in the traditional fashion.

restaurant.name: In2010 Restaurant
restaurant.landmark: Bet. West 10 St. & Christopher St. off 6th Ave,

City Harvest
restaurant.description:
Make a donation to City Harvest with a Delivery.com order! You can help those in need by choosing items from the City Harvest menu. The total cost of your order will be sent as a donation to City Harvest, and help in their efforts to feed NYC's hungry. Upon receipt of your donation, you will be sent an acknowledgment letter from City Harvest.
City Harvest, the world's first and New York City's only food rescue organization, connects good food that would otherwise go to waste with people struggling with hunger. This year they will rescue 28 million pounds of food, helping to feed more than 300,000 men, women and children each week.This order will go directly to City Harvest as a monetary donation. No food will be delivered to you.

restaurant.name: Kosher Deluxe
restaurant.description: Under the strict supervision of Rabbi Amram Roth of Boro Park.

restaurant.name: Kosher Deluxe Catering
restaurant.description: Under the strict supervision of Rabbi Amram Roth of Boro Park.

restaurant.name: Burrito Mariachi
restaurant.description: A restaurant that offers a wide variety of Tex-Mex inspired dishes.

restaurant.name: Red House
restaurant.description: Each NY neighborhood has its own sushi joint, and Red House could be yours! You can't go wrong with all your favorite Chinese dishes on the menu.

restaurant.name: Mamani
restaurant.description: 2/26 - Restaurant is out of fries for the night

restaurant.name: Pomodoro Ristorante & Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Lovers of vodka sauce: rejoice! Pomodoro is using their creamy vodka sauce on penne and on pizzas, too. Pomodoro also serves up appetizers, heros, Italian entrees, and salads. Still craving vodka sauce? You can order it here by the pint.
restaurant.landmark: Between Cleveland Place and Mulberry St.

restaurant.name: Silver Spurs
restaurant.description:
Silver Spurs, 'home of the world's greatest hamburger,' is serving them up by the dozen. Also try one of their imaginatively-named sandwiches, "appeteasers," salads, and omelets. If using a Credit Card to pay for your order:
Please indicate your tip in the special instructions. (Restaurant is unable to acquire tip upon point-of-delivery). Thank you for your cooperation.
In order to process your credit card, Silver Spurs requires that you provide your CVV code. The restaurant will be contacting you after you place your order to obtain this information.
Please note NO requests for substitutions will be honored

restaurant.name: Chelsea Cottage Chinese Restaurant
restaurant.description: Chelsea Cottage Chinese Restaurant uses authentic ingredients to prepare a wide variety of Chinese favorites, from appetizers to noodle dishes, entrees, and more!

restaurant.name: Burger Creations
restaurant.description: Our burgers and specialty sandwiches are carefully prepared from the very best ingredients that are delivered to us daily. Through our commitment to quality and our renowned original recipes, we strive to transform your traditional burger into a premium culinary experience. Enjoy!

restaurant.name: Stromboli Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Stromboli pizzeria is a neighborhood pizza joint that serves up all kinds of pizza slices.

restaurant.name: Pinche Taqueria
restaurant.description: Pinche is a taqueria through-and-through. Here you'll find authentic Mexican food, like tacos and burritos, made using fresh ingredients and seafood, with fresh salsas and sauces made from scratch complementing each dish.

restaurant.name: The Path Cafe Catering
restaurant.description: For your next event or gathering, order a breakfast platter from The Path Cafe Catering! Bagels, pastries, and smoked salmon are all available in a variety of platters. Order hot and cold beverages, as well.

restaurant.name: Friend House
restaurant.description: Friend house is your, well, friendly neighborhood sushi bar. Serving up all the sushi, hand rolls, dumplings, dim sum, noodles, chicken, pork, and Thai food you could ever want, Friend House has got your Asian craving covered.

restaurant.name: Pie by the Pound
restaurant.description: Pie by the Pound serves up a wide array of oblong, very thin-crust pizzas.

restaurant.name: 9 Edo Sushi & Grill
restaurant.description: A popular Village sushi joint, Edo Sushi provides all your favorite rolls, many house specialty rolls, and also a wide array of Japanese entrees.

restaurant.name: Third Ave Blue 9 Burger
restaurant.description: If you want some quality fast-food burgers, head over to Blue 9. Also try their fresh fries and shakes. It's cheap and you won't be disappointed.
restaurant.cuisines: Burgers, Convenience Items, Juice Bar, Beer

restaurant.name: Amici
restaurant.description: Amici is a small pizzeria that serves a wide range of traditional pizzas and specialty pizzas.

restaurant.name: Olympic Pita
restaurant.description: Olympic Pita is a Midtown West kosher staple. The restaurant serves many Israeli and Middle Eastern dishes as well as sushi platters under strict kosher supervision.
restaurant.cuisines: Glatt Kosher, Kosher, OU Kosher, Israeli

restaurant.name: Zen Palate
restaurant.description: This Union Square restaurant emphasizes not only vegetarian cuisine, but a healthy approach to Asian food. For its use of only the healthiest ingredients and its delicious fare, Zen Palate was voted the best vegetarian restaurant in NYC by Vogue.

restaurant.name: Focacceria Catering
restaurant.description: Focaccia sandwiches and pasta dishes form the center point of Focacceria's menu of Italian favorites. Choose one of their specialty catering pasta dishes for your next party or gathering!

restaurant.name: Yawa Sushi
restaurant.description: A tradition sushi spot that has a large menu and provides rolls with intense layers of flavor

restaurant.name: Baluchi's Catering
restaurant.description: Baluchi's, one of Zagat's top rated Indian restaurants, offers a selection of traditional & regional Indian cuisines that are carefully prepared and presented by experienced chefs. Order half and full trays of all your Indian favorites, plus Tandoori breads and beverages, from Baluchi's Catering.

restaurant.name: Bully's
restaurant.description: Bully's is one of your classic American diners in the best tradition: fast food, all your favorites, and a wide selection of foods that are especially great for a no-fuss, satisfying breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

restaurant.name: 28 St. Chef 28
restaurant.description: Delicious Chinese food that is fresh and best of all healthy. Indulge in your favorite Chinese staples and you won't leave feeling like a salty balloon.

restaurant.name: The City Tavern
restaurant.description: The City Tavern specializes in American Traditional comfort food, including pasta, sandwiches, hamburgers, and salads.

restaurant.name: Wine Therapy
restaurant.description: Wine Therapy offers a wide selection of specialty and organic wines from around the world, and prides itself in offering lesser-known wines from small producers.

restaurant.name: Village Farm & Grocery (open 24/7)
restaurant.description: Village Farm and Grocery is a convenient grocery store, open 24/7, that delivers produce, sandwiches, ice creams, beverages, and household items.Please allow Three HOURS for delivery for any orders ABOVE 35th or BELOW BROOME Street. For orders in Brooklyn, please allow up to Four (4) HOURS for delivery. CREDIT CARD MUST BE PRESENT AT THE TIME OF DELIVERY. Please note that if you are not available to receive the order, Village Farm will charge a fee to your Credit Card no greater than 15% of the total amount.

restaurant.name: 2nd Ave Deli
restaurant.description: A classic New York deli that gives Kosher food justice. Traditional kosher fare that could rival any Jewish grandmother's home cooked goods as well as other more modern food means that no matter how you order, you will fall in love with 2nd Ave Deli.

restaurant.name: Eileen's Cheesecake
restaurant.description: A picture may be worth a thousand words but it can't compare to the creamy taste of Eileen's delectable cheesecakes. Ordering is easy, fast, and the memory of these cakes will last. Send the perfect treat to a loved one or yourself today!$1.00 extra to write on cheesecakes
restaurant.landmark: Corner of Kenamre & Centre Opposite Lafayette & Spring

restaurant.name: East River Liquors
restaurant.description: IMPORTANT - PLEASE NOTE: Credit card must be presented at the time of delivery so the restaurant can obtain an imprint and signature. They may also require proper identification that matches the credit card holder.

restaurant.name: Beacon Wines & Spirits
restaurant.description: This Upper West Side liquor store boasts a wide selection of alcoholic beverages for budgets big and small. Upon checkout, please include your billing address in the delivery instructions field. Beacon Wines & Spirits also requires that you provide the CVV code from the back of your credit card. They will be contacting you after you place your order to obtain this information. We also recommend that your credit card be presented at the time of delivery so the merchant can obtain an imprint and signature. They may also require proper identification that matches the credit card hold

restaurant.name: 10th Ave Wine & Liquors
restaurant.description: IMPORTANT - PLEASE NOTE: Credit card must be presented at the time of delivery so the merchant can obtain an imprint and signature. They may also require proper identification that matches the credit card holder.

restaurant.name: Gracie's Wines
restaurant.description: Gracie's Wines features an eclectic selection of wines from across the globe at varying prices. Don't be surprised to stumble upon a hard-to-find liquor in this small wine shop!

restaurant.name: Pita City Catering
restaurant.description: Believing that great health and great taste can be obtained at the same time, Pita City Falafel opened in 1996 in hopes of promoting a distinct kind of healthy cuisine to Chelsea. Pita City presents wholesome Syrian food with friendly service and atmosphere. Pita City's menu features the highest quality ingredients served family style, and the results are scrumptious.

restaurant.name: Green Cafe Catering
restaurant.description: At Green Cafe there really is something for everyone to enjoy. Menu options range from sandwiches and wraps to salads and paninis.

restaurant.name: Fine & Schapiro
restaurant.description: For over 80 years, Fine & Schapiro have served traditional Jewish food. You can order anything from a quick deli sandwich to a full Kosher meal at this gourmet eatery. Kosher Food Under Rabbinical Supervision of Israel Mayer Steinberg

restaurant.name: Ritz Asia Fusion Catering
restaurant.description: Asian Fusion takes center stage at Ritz Asia, where a combination of Japanese, Chinese, and Thai specialties are on the extensive menu. Order from a wide array of appetizers, dim sum, sushi, noodles, and gourmet entrees.
